label.value: pattern specification involved in metanephros development

value.value: Any developmental process that results in the creation of defined areas or spaces within the metanephros to which cells respond and eventually are instructed to differentiate.
The process in which the anatomical structures of the metanephric nephron are generated and organized. A metanephric nephron is the functional unit of the metanephros.

The process in which the anatomical structures of a metanephric nephron tubule are generated and organized. A metanephric nephron tubule is an epithelial tube that is part of the metanephric nephron, the functional part of the metanephros.

The process in which the anatomical structures of the metanephric renal vesicle are generated and organized. The renal vesicle is the primordial structure of the metanephric nephron epithelium, and is formed by the condensation of mesenchymal cells.

label.value: mesenchymal to epithelial transition involved in metanephric renal vesicle formation

value.value: A transition where a mesenchymal cell establishes apical/basolateral polarity,forms intercellular adhesive junctions, synthesizes basement membrane components and becomes an epithelial cell that will contribute to the shaping of the metanephric renal vesicle.

The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a metanephric nephron tubule from unspecified parts. A metanephric nephron tubule is an epithelial tube that is part of a nephron in the metanephros.

label.value: epithelial cell migration involved in metanephric nephron tubule morphogenesis

value.value: The orderly movement of epithelial cells within a renal tubule that contributes to metanephric nephron tubule morphogenesis.

label.value: regulation of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process involved in metanephric nephron morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the occurrence or rate of mesenchymal stem cell death by apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of the nephron in the metanephros.

label.value: negative regulation of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process involved in metanephric nephron morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that reduces the occurrence or rate of mesenchymal stem cell death by apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of the nephron in the metanephros.

label.value: positive regulation of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process involved in metanephric nephron morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that increases the occurrence or rate of mesenchymal stem cell death by apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of the nephron in the metanephros.

label.value: regulation of metanephric nephron tubule epithelial cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of metanephric nephron tubule epithelial cell differentiation.

label.value: negative regulation of metanephric nephron tubule epithelial cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of metanephric nephron tubule epithelial cell differentiation.

label.value: mesenchymal stem cell maintenance involved in metanephric nephron morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which an organism retains a population of mesenchymal stem cells that contributes to the shaping of a nephron in the metanephros. A mesenchymal stem cell is a cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized mesenchymal cells.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of monocarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (-COOH) group.
The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of monocarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (-COOH) group.
The directed movement of compounds that contain sulfur, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the circulatory system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The circulatory system is the organ system that passes nutrients (such as amino acids and electrolytes), gases, hormones, blood cells, etc. to and from cells in the body to help fight diseases and help stabilize body temperature and pH to maintain homeostasis.

The progression of the vascular cord over time from its initial formation until its mature state. The vascular cord is the primordial vasculature that will develop into blood vessels by the process of tubulogenesis.

The directed movement of an organelle along a microtubule, mediated by motor proteins. This process begins with the attachment of an organelle to a microtubule, and ends when the organelle reaches its final destination.
The process in which ammonium is transported across a membrane. Ammonium is the cation NH4+.

definition.value: Note that this term is not intended for use in annotating lateral movement within membranes.

value.value: The reproductive developmental process whose specific outcome is the progression of the seminiferous tubule over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Seminiferous tubules are ducts located in the testicles, and are the specific location of meiosis, and the subsequent creation of gametes, namely spermatozoa.
A change in the morphology or behavior of a fibroblast resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand.

A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a type B pancreatic cell to attain its fully functional state. A type B pancreatic cell is a cell located towards center of the islets of Langerhans that secretes insulin.

definition.value: These processes continue to 60 DPA in Gossypium spp.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in liver morphogenesis

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the shaping of the liver.
The process in which the anatomical structures of the liver are generated and organized.
Any apoptotic process in an endothelial cell. An endothelial cell comprises the outermost layer or lining of anatomical structures and can be squamous or cuboidal.
The chemical reactions and pathways involving diatomic oxygen (O2).

label.value: establishment of protein localization to organelle

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location on or in an organelle. Encompasses establishment of localization in the membrane or lumen of a membrane-bounded organelle.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location in a membrane.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location in the plasma membrane.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a location in a vacuole.

label.value: establishment of protein localization to vacuole

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in a vacuole.
The movement of a lymphocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body.
The movement of a T cell within or between different tissues and organs of the body.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, the cell cortex.
A cellular protein localization process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a location within the microtubule cytoskeleton.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways within a cell or an organism involving those compounds formed as a part of the normal anabolic and catabolic processes. These processes take place in most, if not all, cells of the organism.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to stress. Response to stress is a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a disturbance in organismal or cellular homeostasis, usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

definition.value: Note that this term is in the subset of terms that should not be used for direct gene product annotation. Instead, select a child term or, if no appropriate child term exists, please request a new term. Direct annotations to this term may be amended during annotation QC.

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of fertilization. Fertilization is the union of gametes of opposite sexes during the process of sexual reproduction to form a zygote. It involves the fusion of the gametic nuclei (karyogamy) and cytoplasm (plasmogamy).
The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of the extracellular matrix.
An action potential that occurs in a cardiac muscle cell.
An action potential that occurs in a sinoatrial node cardiac muscle cell.
An action potential that occurs in an atrioventricular node cardiac muscle cell.
An action potential that occurs in a Purkinje myocyte.

label.value: SA node cell to atrial cardiac muscle cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from an SA node cardiomyocyte to an atrial cardiomyocyte.

label.value: cell-cell signaling involved in cardiac conduction

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another and contributes to the heart process that regulates cardiac muscle contraction; beginning with the generation of an action potential in the sinoatrial node and ending with regulation of contraction of the myocardium.

label.value: AV node cell to bundle of His cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from an AV node cardiac muscle cell to a bundle of His cardiomyocyte.

label.value: Purkinje myocyte to ventricular cardiac muscle cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from a Purkinje myocyte to a ventricular cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: cell communication involved in cardiac conduction

value.value: Any process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings that contributes to the process of cardiac conduction. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label.value: AV node cell to bundle of His cell communication

value.value: The process that mediates interactions between an AV node cell and its surroundings that contributes to the process of the AV node cell communicating with a bundle of His cell in cardiac conduction. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.
